The average price per litre for liquid milk in both the organized and unorganized segments are expected to rise from ₹ 45 per litre and ₹ 42 per litre in 2015, respectively, to ₹ 71 per litre and ₹ 66 per litre in 2020, respectively.

Around 45% of the total liquid milk is consumed in northern India, with Uttar Pradesh, Rajasthan, Punjab and Haryana being the larger markets. Key markets in western and central India include Gujarat, Maharashtra and Madhya Pradesh while south India includes Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu and Karnataka as the top consumers. Bihar and West Bengal are the major milk consuming states in eastern India.

