## Flavoured Milk

The flavoured milk market is currently one of the fastest growing segments in the Indian dairy industry, growing at a CAGR of approximately 26% during 2007 to 2014, reaching sales revenues of ₹ 12.6 billion in 2014. The annual consumption of flavoured milk is expected to grow at a CAGR of 14% from 134 million litres in 2015 to 259 million litres in 2020. Total consumption value of flavoured milk is also expected to increase from ₹ 15.9 billion in 2015 to ₹ 47.8 billion in 2020.

